The Shady Trader
[trigger settlement]
[tier 1]

A figure in an oversized coat leans against the wall of the general store, half-hidden behind a stack of crates. He catches your eye and beckons with a ringed finger. "Psst. You look like someone who values their time."

He flips open the coat. The lining is sewn with dozens of pockets, each bulging with gear. Daggers, armor plates, rolled bundles of leather and steel. More equipment than should physically fit on one person.

"Don't ask where I got it," he says. "Don't ask how it all fits in the coat. Just tell me what kind of traveler you are, and I'll set you up. Five hundred gold, flat rate. No haggling, no questions."

choices:

* "I'm an outdoorsman" = A sturdy kit for the self-sufficient traveler
  He sizes you up and nods. "Practical type. I respect that." He reaches into the coat and produces, one by one: a hunting knife with a horn handle, a suit of lamellar armor still smelling of the tanner's oil, a pair of heavy trail boots, a good waterskin, a dog-eared copy of something called "A Guide to the Borderlands," and an ornate spyglass that he handles with surprising care.

  "Everything you need to live off the land and talk your way out of what the land throws at you." He fans the items across a crate like a card dealer. "Five hundred. Take it or leave it."

  You take it.
  +give_gold 500
  +add_item hunting_knife
  +add_item lamellar
  +add_item trail_boots
  +add_item waterskin
  +add_item peoples_borderlands
  +add_item ornate_spyglass

* "I solve problems with steel" = The best arms and armor money can buy
  "A direct approach. I like it." He pulls a gleaming arming sword from somewhere inside the coat, followed by a brigandine that clinks heavily as he sets it down, trail boots with reinforced soles, and then the same assortment of field gear: waterskin, guidebook, spyglass.

  "You'll cut through anything the plains throw at you, and the pack gear keeps you standing between fights." He stacks it all neatly. "Five hundred for the lot."

  You don't need to be asked twice.
  +give_gold 500
  +add_item arming_sword
