* "Give me the good stuff" = Gear that shouldn't exist in any shop
  His eyes widen, then narrow. He glances left, glances right, and leans in close. "You're one of those, are you? Alright." He reaches deep into the coat, past the normal pockets, past what should be the back of the coat, and keeps reaching. His arm disappears to the shoulder.

  He pulls out a Revathi labrys that hums faintly in the air. Then a suit of armor stamped with the crest of the 17th Mountain Regiment, which has been missing for forty years. Then a pair of windstrider boots that seem to weigh nothing at all. The field gear comes last, almost as an afterthought.

  "Don't tell anyone where you got these," he says. "Especially not the 17th Mountain Regiment."
